\displaystyle \binom{n}{k}=\binom{n-1}{k} + \binom{n-1}{k-1}
\displaystyle \left(1+x\right)^{n} = \left(1+x\right)\left(1+x\right)^{n-1}
\binom{n-1}{n} = 0
\binom{-1}{n} = 0
x^k
\left(1+x\right)^{n} = \left(1+x\right)\left(1+x\right)^{n-1}
\sum_{k=0}^n \binom{n}{k} x^k = \left(1+x\right)\sum_{k=0}^{n-1} \binom{n-1}{k} x^k
\left(\sum_{k=0}^{n-1} \binom{n-1}{k} x^k \right)+\left(\sum_{k=0}^{n-1} \binom{n-1}{k} x^{k+1} \right) = \left(\sum_{k=0}^{n} \binom{n-1}{k} x^k \right)+\left(\sum_{k=0}^{n} \binom{n-1}{k-1} x^{k}\right)
\sum_{k=0}^n \binom{n}{k} x^k = \sum_{k=0}^{n} \left(\binom{n-1}{k} + \binom{n-1}{k-1}\right) x^k
\displaystyle \binom{n}{k}=\binom{n-1}{k} + \binom{n-1}{k-1}.
